        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Bah, some of you need to get off the "VI hates us" thing already.  It's starting to sound like some of the things Seru faction NPCs say (interesting side note: ask one such NPC "who is abashi" ;)).</P><P>In any case, I would think/hope that VI's problem isn't so much that they don't know how to do it, but don't know how best to do it without screwing other things up.  I would imagine the mob's buff list would have to be expanded, for one (15 slots isn't enough for all the debuffs + dots now)...</P><P>Also, about debuff dots...why not just have the first, say, Cessation create an effect that does damage, but have the rest not?  That way you could still use it as a decent fast dot (albeit one with major aggro).</P><P>Or...and this could help shaman / chanters far more than us, but I think it's worth mentioning...what if the first debuff landed had 100% of its debuff effectiveness, then the next did 50%, then the next 25%, etc.?  100-50-25-12.5-etc. approaches 200% as you add more and more debuffers, but never reaches it; thus you'd never have more than twice the normal debuff effectiveness, but would always have *some* use for another debuffing class.  And for debuff dots like Cessation, you could have them do their full damage even if they did only partial debuffing.</P><P>Of course, having a mob slowed twice what it is now, or having its MR debuffed twice, or any debuff that has a huge effect, would make things a little too easy...would be unlikely to happen unless they nerfed the base effectiveness of such spells, at least on raid level mobs (yuck).  But, a thought...</P><P><img src="http://members.aol.com/jrimdziustemp/chickencult.gif">   Aatudien, 58 necromancer of Lanys T'Vyl</font></td>
