      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Kaeric Gath</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> VI does have the ability to fix DoT stacking.  Will they?  Probably not.  There is a mentality that I'd like to just heap on VI, but I can't.  There is a mind set in the game industry that seems to be pretty prevelent.  Programmers don't check their code and do shoddy work.  It's a quick solution, but causes more problems than it fixes and then when the deed gets dicovered, they hide behind time estimates.  It takes roughly 10 times as long to rip out the offending code and fix it then it did to do their hack.  They dhould have done it right in the first place, but didn't.  Designers do it too, they change data and don't tell anyone, artist check in bad models and don't tell anyone.  QA gets left in the dark long enough and they just get apathetic, if they even know what they are doing (I'm not even going there, needless to say, I don't have a high opinion of VI QA).  It all comes down to laziness.  EQ has it's place in the limelight and they thing they have a monopoly on the on-line gaming market.  As long as they think so, they are going to keep doing what has worked in the past, and it's not to our advantage.  One thing that they do not do, that is much to their disadvantage is to listen to the fan base.  Kelly Flock already stated it, all he cares about is whether or not we have a valid credit card number.  Until this also changes, we can't expect too many worthwhile attempts at fixing the class balance of the necro.  </P><P>Another thing we suffer from is the anti-necro stigma that permeates a lot of servers.  There were a lot of lamers (herein called "uberwhiners") that made necros when we were overpowered.  They totally ruined our image, when we got nerfed, they abandoned their necros for the next "uber class".  We get stuck holding a bag of old dung.  That is another big reason why we are just "twitch bitches" in raids.  We have so many abilities, but we keep getting hammered down because people think they know our class.  While we still need fixing, we still are fairly potent in the hands of a good player that knows how to use his power to the best advantage.  </P><P>What's the fix?  To tell you the truth, I don't know.  I mean we all have ideas, and I guess the best thing is to throw them out and keep throwing them out until VI looks at it's process and improves it.  Personally, I have a couple ideas that I think might be worth looking at, but I won't be the judge.  You, my peers, are far better qualified than I.</P><P>1)  Wizards have a lure and bane series of spells, why not do something similar for the necros?  A kind of lure/bane DoT, that does decent damage over a short period of time.</P><P>2)  Yes, we need FD upgraded and working properly.  It's stupid that I can FD and lose agro, have a mob wander off and reagro on me with a bunch of his friends when I stand back up.</P><P>3)  Lifetaps, make them unresistable again, or pretty close too.  The casting times make ensure that we can't just keep taping and taping until something is nuked to dead.  We don't have the HP to stand up to that kind of agro either.  Let's face it, most mobs at high levels have too many hp for this to be a danger, unless 100 necros all decide to do an epic mob.  </P><P>4)  Remove EE, make them vendor items, or make them non comsumeable.  </P><P>5)  Give us the ability to make our pet non agro from the start, not an AA skill</P><P>6)  Maybe an inate resistance to some of the insta death spells, like HT and necro class spells.  Not total, but just something of a bonus. </P><P>7)  Oh yes, and ST upgrade too.</P><P>9)  Lower the casting times of our DD spells, they aren't THAT powerful.</P><P>10)  Lower the casting times of some of our DoTs, not a whole lot, but just a second or two.</P><P>11)  Decrease the amount of time that it takes for a DoT to run through it's course of damage.  Not a whole lot, but enough to make us a viable grouping class.  We already have enough downtime for meeding as casters.</P><P>Also, whatever upgrade we recive should be spell/ability upgrades, not just some new item.  EQ has already shown that an item based system just doesn't work.  It's turns into a case of the "haves" vs. the "have nots".  Just some thoughts and observations.  Good hunting my friends.</P><P></P><P>Kaeric Gath<BR>52nd Necromancer of Bertoxxulous<BR>E'Ci<BR>We shall defend our class whatever the cost may be; we shall kite on beaches, newbie grounds, in the Karana's, in streets and on the Qeynos hills. We shall never surrender...</P><P>Edited by - kaeric gath on 04/10/2002  04:14:44</P><P>Edited by - kaeric gath on 04/10/2002  04:16:20</P><P>Edited by - kaeric gath on 04/10/2002  04:18:15</P><P>Edited by - kaeric gath on 04/10/2002  04:25:24</font></td>
